sentinel.led
Class Not

java.lang.Object
  |

        |
        +--sentinel.led.Composite

              +--sentinel.led.Not
public class Not
extends Composite

The Not class denotes an event node for the composite event operator NOT. It contains the event tables for the left and right children as well as references to the left, middle and right event nodes. There is not event table for middle event because the propagated event does not contain the middle event occurrences. The notify() method contains logic for detecting the event according to the semantics of the operator. The NOT event is detected when the right event occurs and the middle event does not occur in the interval formed by the occurrences of the left and right events.

notify

public void notify(Notifiable event,
                   java.lang.Thread parent,
                   Scheduler scheduler)
This method contains the detection logic according to the semantics of the NOT operator. When the middle event is notified, the left event table is cleaned. The right event table is cleaned when the left event is notified.
